描述: Protective stop: The robot was powered off last time due to a joint position disagreement
说明:
Verify that the robot position in the 3D graphics matches the real robot, to ensure that the encoders function before releasing the brakes. Stand back and monitor the robot performing its first program cycle as expected.

  • If the position is not correct, the robot must be repaired. In this case, click Power Off Robot.
  • If the position is correct, please tick the check box below the 3D graphics and click Robot Position Verified

描述: Protective stop: Large movement of the robot detected while it was powered off. The joints were moved while it was powered off, or the encoders do not function.
说明:
Verify that the robot position in the 3D graphics matches the real robot, to ensure that the encoders function before releasing the brakes. Stand back and monitor the robot performing its first program cycle as expected.

  • If the position is not correct, the robot must be repaired. In this case, click Power Off Robot.
  • If the position is correct, please tick the check box below the 3D graphics and click Robot Position Verified
